OL,5, The average annual grocery bill in the 
OL,6, UK is set to rise by #380 this year,   
OL,7, according to research firm Kantar.     
OL,9,FThat means shoppers could be paying on 
OL,10,Faverage an extra #32 a month for food  
OL,11,Fand other groceries.                   
OL,13,FBack in April, the firm predicted the  
OL,14,Fcost of the average annual supermarket 
OL,15,Fshop would go up by #271 in 2022.      
OL,17,FThe upward revision shows "just how    
OL,18,Fsharp price increases have been        
OL,19,Frecently and the impact inflation is   
OL,20,Fhaving on the sector", said Kantar.    
